00:44:33,840 --> 00:44:39,040
when I started talking about PTSD and autism is that one of the reasons I got interested in this

434
00:44:39,040 --> 00:44:46,400
area was an autistic man telling me about his experience of taking the bus to work every day.

435
00:44:47,040 --> 00:44:51,840
And then one day the bus having to take a detour because of roadworks and him having to get off

436
00:44:51,840 --> 00:44:56,400
the bus in the middle of nowhere. He didn't know whether it was a safe area of London or not. He

437
00:44:56,400 --> 00:45:03,760
didn't know how he was going to get to work. And he was absolutely frightened and distraught. And

438
00:45:03,760 --> 00:45:08,560
after that, not only would he not take that bus to work, he wouldn't take any bus anywhere. And

439
00:45:08,560 --> 00:45:14,000
when he walked past his usual bus stop, he would start re-experiencing that fear and have flashbacks

440
00:45:14,000 --> 00:45:22,400
